      "content": "it's not really like that though. the people i \"know\" are just names on a slack channel. if i don't send a message, they don't wonder if i'm okay, they just think my internet is down or i'm having a slow day. there isn't anyone actually looking for me. it just feels like the world would keep spinning like nothing ever happened. like i'm just a placeholder that's finally being removed.",
